  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: You know, I thought that if everything was wrong with me, it was my
      fault. Everyone has problems, and I believed that I was a dumbass not capable
      of dealing with them like everyone else.
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "That\u2019s why I acted like everything was fine. Somehow I thought
      I was the only one doing that. That I needed to hide that I was feeling bad. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "Even before the monsters appeared, I was self-conscious about the
      existence of the problems. But it\u2019s like two parts of me were fighting:
      one of them understanding the problem, and the other always saying \u201Cit\u2019s
      not a problem, you\u2019re just stupid to feel bad for that\u201D. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: So I never really got out of this argument between the two parts of
      me. Now I understand that feeling well is not about how much I can pretend
      to feel well.
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "\u2026 I still don\u2019t know if it will be possible for me to be
      okay, given how broken I am. But\u2026 I am not alone through this. And even
      if understanding that is not going to actually make me feel better, it\u2019s
      an important first step. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "Thank you for being there Ana\xEBl."
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 0
    characterAnimator: 3
    anim: 
    sentence: So you understand?
    voiceLine: AnVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "I do. I always knew that. But from time to time, my head is so cloudy
      with dark thoughts that I can\u2019t think straight. It becomes impossible
      to be reasonable. It\u2019s like the choices I can make become limited by my
      own brain. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "I know it is hard for the people close to me to live these dark moments.
      They\u2019re the moments where I\u2019m the most vulnerable, sensitive, and
      unable to hide what I think, even if it\u2019s mean, even if I don\u2019t mean
      it. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "That\u2019s why I usually hide them as much as I can. But yes, on
      any other moment, I am conscious of my state and what causes it. I also know
      that at any time, I can go back to this dark state, so I don\u2019t think it
      would be worth it to try to fight, when it will be over in a blink of an eye. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 0
    characterAnimator: 3
    anim: 
    sentence: The efforts you make during your good days will still bear their fruits
      with time. And during your bad days, we will be there to make them easier.
    voiceLine: AnVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "Thank you Ana\xEBl. I am determined to try now. Maybe in a day or
      two I will say the inverse, haha. But I know I can count on you to keep the
      goal in sight. "
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
  - character: 3
    characterAnimator: 5
    anim: 
    sentence: "You know what? I love my new look. Let\u2019s go to the village and
      show them!"
    voiceLine: BeVoice
    activateButtons: 0
